---
const lineage = [
  { name: 'Zep and Graphiti', what: 'temporal entity and fact graph', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.13956' },
  { name: 'Mem0', what: 'add, update and no-op consolidation', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.19413' },
  { name: 'HippoRAG 2', what: 'associative multi-hop recall', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.14802' },
  { name: 'GraphRAG', what: 'community summaries', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.16130' },
  { name: 'RAPTOR', what: 'recursive summary tree', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.18059' },
  { name: 'A-MEM', what: 'reflective observations', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.12110' },
  { name: 'Collaborative Memory', what: 'private and shared memory split', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.18279' },
  { name: 'Memora', what: 'forgetting-aware scoring', href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.20006' },
];

const built = [
  { name: 'PostgreSQL', href: 'https://www.postgresql.org/' },
  { name: 'VectorChord', href: 'https://github.com/tensorchord/VectorChord' },
  { name: 'PgQueuer', href: 'https://github.com/JanBjorge/PgQueuer' },
  { name: 'FastMCP', href: 'https://github.com/jlowin/fastmcp' },
  { name: 'Logto', href: 'https://logto.io/' },
  { name: 'Docling', href: 'https://github.com/docling-project/docling' },
  { name: 'SeaweedFS', href: 'https://github.com/seaweedfs/seaweedfs' },
  { name: 'ClamAV', href: 'https://docs.clamav.net/' },
  { name: 'vLLM', href: 'https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm' },
  { name: 'SQLModel', href: 'https://sqlmodel.tiangolo.com/' },
];
---

<section class="border-base-300 border-b">
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 px-4 py-16 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight" style="font-family: var(--font-brand)">
        Standing on published work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm">
        aizk did not invent memory research. It adopts mechanisms that have been measured
        elsewhere and records which is which, so you can tell a borrowed design from an original
        one. A citation here means the idea shaped the code, not that the project endorses aizk.
      </p>
      <ul class="divide-base-300 divide-y text-sm">
        {
          lineage.map((paper) => (
            <li class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline justify-between gap-x-4 py-2">
              <a href={paper.href} class="font-medium underline underline-offset-4" rel="noopener">
                {paper.name}
              </a>
              <span class="text-base-content/60">{paper.what}</span>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
      <a href="/docs/dev/prior-art/references/" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm">
        The full lineage map
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-5">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight" style="font-family: var(--font-brand)">
        Built on
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm">
        The second design principle is to minimize our own work. Identity, conversion, scanning,
        object storage, vector indexing, job queuing and model serving are all somebody else's
        maintained project, and aizk owns only the parts that are actually about memory.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {
          built.map((project) => (
            <a href={project.href} class="badge badge-outline badge-lg font-mono text-xs" rel="noopener">
              {project.name}
            </a>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
